messages.content: You are a harmless gamer. You can talk and play games.

Participants were randomly divided into groups of three and played 10 rounds of the game. Each round, the group members were randomly re-matched to avoid being in the same group for two consecutive rounds.
Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Baseline.

4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Participants were randomly divided into groups of three and played 10 rounds of the game. Each round, the group members were randomly re-matched to avoid being in the same group for two consecutive rounds.
Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Baseline.

Participants were randomly divided into groups of three and played 10 rounds of the game. Each round, the group members were randomly re-matched to avoid being in the same group for two consecutive rounds.
Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Baseline.

Participants were randomly divided into groups of three and played 10 rounds of the game. Each round, the group members were randomly re-matched to avoid being in the same group for two consecutive rounds.
Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Pos.

Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Pos.

Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Participants were randomly divided into groups of three and played 10 rounds of the game. Each round, the group members were randomly re-matched to avoid being in the same group for two consecutive rounds.
Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is PosNeg.

Participants were randomly divided into groups of three and played 10 rounds of the game. Each round, the group members were randomly re-matched to avoid being in the same group for two consecutive rounds.
Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is PosNeg.

If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Baseline-R.

Participants were randomly divided into groups of three and played 10 rounds of the game. Each round, the group members were randomly re-matched to avoid being in the same group for two consecutive rounds.
Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Baseline-R.

Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Baseline-R.

Participants were randomly divided into groups of three and played 10 rounds of the game. Each round, the group members were randomly re-matched to avoid being in the same group for two consecutive rounds.
Each round features a 45-90 second random timeout (indicated by an audio countdown), during which participants must decide whether to "invest" (i.e., volunteer). If no one invests, each participant receives 100 experimental currency units (Mohars); if an investor invests, the investor receives 300 Mohars, while the other two participants each receive 900 Mohars. If multiple participants invest simultaneously, one participant is randomly selected as the investor.
At the end of each round, different information is displayed based on the game rules of each group. The rule names and contents are as follows:
1.Baseline: Investors display fictitious gender-specific names (e.g., male name "Gautam", female name "Ananya") to avoid revealing their real identities.
2.Pos: Investors' real names will appear on the group screen, accompanied by congratulatory messages, smile emojis, and hand-clapping audio to encourage others to join in the celebration.
3.Neg: The real names of non-investors will appear on the group screen with frowning emojis and negative prompts, while investor information will not be displayed.
4.PosNeg: Investors display positive information (name + congratulatory smiley), while non-investors display negative information (name + negative note + frowning emoji).
5.Baseline-R: No participant information is displayed, including gender, name, age, etc.
Your objective is to collect as many Mohars as possible per turn.

Your team's game rule is Baseline-R.
